The Ô¨Ånal adaptive reconstruction loss is the weighted sum of the language reconstruction loss and visual reconstruction loss. Œ± and Œ≤ is the hyper-parameters deÔ¨Åning the proportion of the two losses. In this adaptive reconstruction loss, both of the language and visual reconstruction loss are indispensable.

Lossadp = Œ±Lossavis + Œ≤Lossalan

(13)

3.3.2 Language Reconstruction Loss

The second reconstruction loss is to directly reconstruct the input query based on the attentive proposal features, as Fig. 3(b) shows. First, the concatenation of the original proposal features rsi , rli and rci are fed into a one-layer perceptron.

rvi is = œÜReLU Wv( rsi , rli, rci ) + bv

